==Bundles==
Red Mushroom is used in the {{Bundle|Dye||y}}, and is one of the options for the {{Bundle|Exotic||y}}.

==Recipes==
Despite the numbers listed on the tooltip, the [[Life Elixir]] will fully restore [[Health]] to maximum regardless of how low it is.
{{Recipes|header|hide=buff,duration}}
{{:Life Elixir|RecipeRow/NoBuffs}}
{{Recipes|footer}}

==Tailoring==
Red Mushroom is used in the spool of the [[2 Willow Lane#Sewing Machine|Sewing Machine]] to create the {{name|Spotted Headscarf|class=inline}}. It can also be used as a red dye color at the dye pots in [[Emily]]'s and [[Haley]]'s house, located at [[2 Willow Lane]].

==Quests==
*The Red Mushroom may be randomly requested during any season at the [[Quests#Help Wanted Quests|"Help Wanted" board]] outside [[Pierre's General Store]] for a reward of {{Price|225}} and 150 [[Friendship]] points.
*2-3 Red Mushrooms may be requested by [[Catfish]], [[Spook Fish]], or [[Woodskip]] in a [[Fish Pond#Quests|Fish Pond quest]] to increase the capacity of the pond from 3 to 5.

==Bugs==
While playing local co-op on the switch, if the player or a farmhand has had [[Energy|exhaustion]] the previous day and consumes a poisonous item that reduces their energy to zero (or below), the game will softlock.

